<p style="text-align:justify;">me something of this secret &#8211; which he did with great reluctance as follows &#8211; Having asked him how he thought the world was made and peopled &#8211; the Chipeweans, replied he, believe that at first there was no Earth &#8211; that all was one awful Ocean, inhabited with no living creature &#8211; excepting a mighty Bird which descended from above &#8211; it seemed all on fire &#8211; its eyes were like lightening &#8211; its wings sounded like thunder &#8211; it touched the sea &#8211; the Earth emerged from the deep and remained on the surface as it now stands &#8211; then it touched the Earth which produced Animals, and from Dogs came Chipeweans<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  In that I believe you should speak truth, observed I gravely<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Yes, continued he seriously &#8211; for that is the reason we never eat the flesh of that animal.  I next enquired of him what became of that mighty Bird.</p>

